	<section id="Glossarytermnospacesorformatting">
		<h2>Padding</h2>
		<p>In CSS, padding is the space between the element and any borders around it. You can specify padding for the top, right, bottom, 
    and left of the element individually, using three values (top, right & left, bottom), two values (top & bottom, right & left),
    or one value for all four sides. 
			<cite>Definition adapted from <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/css/css_padding.asp">“CSS Padding.” CSS Padding, W3Schools, www.w3schools.com/css/css_padding.asp.</a> by <span class="contributor">Olivia Carey</span>
				</cite>
				</p>
</section>
